Text: It's so good. The way Nicki says the words, they flow so smoothly. She's such a lyrical genius it's insane. Also, the lyrics themselves are so good. The effects are amazing, such as the ringing bell and the horn. The instruments are amazing, the "ting" of the cymbals, the trumpet, percussion projecting her words, the beat, the synthesizer, and the clapping too. It's so good. The saying "hey" and "damn" in the background is such a good touch to the piece as well. The storytelling is amazing, the song has been viewed by some as a diss track, in answer to "Baby Got Back". Whereas Sir Mix-a-Lot focuses on a woman's body and the pleasure it gives him, Minaj raps from the perspective of the unnamed woman and shows how she uses her body to profit and empower herself. It's so different from some of her other, newer songs too, such as BANG and Super Freaky Girl, which are both SUPER GOOD, but I just love how this song differentiates from others. It's also very different from some other female singers, such as Selena Gomez or Arianna Grande, which is cool too. She's just so different with storytelling and music, especially in this piece of music. Also,  the song peaked at number two on the US Billboard Hot 100, becoming Minaj's highest-charting single at the time. The song also peaked within the top ten in Australia, Canada, Ireland, New Zealand, and the United Kingdom, the top forty in Austria, France, and Portugal, and the top fifty in the Czech Republic. Also, the art and photography of the cover are great as well, it's simplistic and not too provocative, but also doesn't take away from Nicki's more "PG-13" style of music.

I saw a plate left on the table with tin foil covering it. "Oh, did you make some food to eat when you got home?" the girl asked. "No, I didn't. I think mummy must have left this for me," I replied. I walked over and lifted the tin foil. It was a plate of turkey dinosaurs and potato smiles ready to be reheated. Nice. I took the girl upstairs towards my room. "Now stay quiet, daddy has enough trouble sleeping with mummy's CPAP machine going all night. She has really bad sleep apnea," I warned. The girl nodded and quickly tiptoed with me past their bedroom door. When we got into my dark room, the glow-in-the-dark stars on the ceiling were the first to draw the eye. I always thought space was cool and I'd hope any girl worth my time would think the same. I then turned the light on so she didn't trip over my Power Rangers figures I had been playing with before I left. I saw here staring at my PC below my Danny Phantom poster.
